name: ethyl 5,6-dimethoxyindole-2-carboxylate
Reason: Base compound, indole has a melting point of around 52°C. Considering the functional groups, - Ethyl ester (COOEt) group: +40°C, due to increased molecular weight and polarity. - Methoxy groups (2x OCH3): +2x30°C, as they increase polarity and potential for intermolecular hydrogen bonding. - Direct attachment of substituents to the aromatic ring typically raises the melting point due to more rigid structure.
